The course helps to understand the population and settlement development of Estonia, Europe and the world.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to build a theoretical outline for the study of population, develop the skills for population analysis, and introduce the basic concept and issues of demography.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, the student: * knows the main population concepts, processes and regularities * understands the population processes related to different population groups * is able to compile basic analyses and prediction for population processes * understands regularities in settlement system and development and the impacts of urban and regional planning on the development of population and settlement geographies
